    "summary": "The Republic of China was formally proclaimed on January 1, 1912, following the [[event:3320|Xinhai Revolution]] that overthrew the Qing dynasty. Sun Yat-sen was inaugurated as provisional president in Nanjing, articulating the three principles of nationalism, democracy, and people's livelihood as the republic's foundational ideology. However, the new republic quickly ceded power to Yuan Shikai, whose military strength was deemed necessary to negotiate the emperor's abdication and prevent civil war.\n\nThe republic proved deeply unstable. Yuan Shikai's attempts to establish personal rule and restore imperial government with himself as emperor failed and accelerated political fragmentation. After Yuan's death in 1916, China entered the warlord era, with competing military commanders controlling different regions and the nominal republican government in Beijing reduced to a facade. The Republic of China remained formally recognized by foreign powers but had little actual authority over most of the country.\n\nSun Yat-sen reorganized his Kuomintang (Nationalist Party) with Soviet assistance in the early 1920s and launched the Northern Expedition in 1926 to reunify China. After Sun's death in 1925, Chiang Kai-shek took command and by 1928 had nominally unified China under Nationalist rule, though the subsequent [[event:2710|Chinese Civil War]] with the Communists and the Japanese invasion challenged Nationalist authority throughout. The Republic of China government relocated to Taiwan in 1949 following Communist victory on the mainland and continues to govern Taiwan.",
